# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in. Bun auto-loads .env at daemon startup.
# None of these are required for a normal run — every one has a sane default.

# Preferred API/UI port. The daemon hops to the next free port if this one's busy and
# records where it landed in ~/.ccmanagerui/runtime.json (see PORT_FIXED below to disable
# the hop).
# PORT=7787

# Bind host for the daemon.
# HOST=127.0.0.1

# Config dir override (holds runtime.json + the instance-identity cache).
# Default: ~/.ccmanagerui
# CCMANAGERUI_HOME=

# sqlite db path override (queue/dispatch/scheduler/accounts state).
# Default: server/data/ccmanagerui.db
# CCMANAGERUI_DB=

# 1 = bind PORT exactly and skip the single-instance guard / port-hop machinery. Useful for
# CI or running two instances deliberately side by side.
# CCMANAGERUI_PORT_FIXED=1

# If set, POST /api/shutdown requires a matching x-ccmanagerui-shutdown-token header (the
# tray sets this itself when it starts the daemon).
# CCMANAGERUI_SHUTDOWN_TOKEN=

# 1 = dispatch uses the harmless fake `claude` CLI stand-in (server/src/fake-claude.ts)
# instead of spawning the real CLI. Use this to exercise dispatch/parse/stream/status
# without spending quota or touching real repos.
# CCMANAGERUI_FAKE=1

# How a queued `claude` run's detached supervisor is launched (server/src/dispatch.ts). A run must
# OUTLIVE quitting/auto-updating the app, which on Windows requires launching it OUTSIDE the daemon's
# job object. Values:
#   wmi   (Windows default) launch via WMI Win32_Process.Create — the ONLY method that survives a
#         tray Quit / auto-update on Windows. Needs PowerShell + WMI (standard on Windows).
#   start ESCAPE HATCH for a machine where WMI/PowerShell is blocked or misbehaving: launch via
#         `cmd /c start` instead. Dispatch still works, but a run will NOT survive quitting the app
#         (a console child stays in the daemon's job object and dies with it).
#   posix (macOS/Linux default) plain detached setsid; there is no job-object problem there.
# Leave unset for the correct per-OS default. Only set it if WMI is unavailable on your box.
# CCMANAGERUI_RUNNER_LAUNCH=wmi

# Force the /api/desktop-install detection result (dev/testing the Instances-tab warning):
# msix-only = MSIX build only (warning shows) · none = nothing installed · ok = classic install.
# CCMANAGERUI_FAKE_DESKTOP_INSTALL=msix-only

# Base URL / port the bundled MCP stdio server (server/src/mcp.ts) uses to reach the
# daemon, instead of reading it from the runtime pointer. CCMANAGERUI_URL wins if both are set.
# CCMANAGERUI_URL=http://127.0.0.1:7787
# CCMANAGERUI_PORT=7787

# 1 = enable the background auto-update loop (git pull --ff-only + reinstall/rebuild +
# self-relaunch on a timer). Off by default; a dirty working tree is never touched.
# CCMANAGERUI_RELAUNCH is set internally by the daemon when it spawns its own successor
# process after an applied update — you shouldn't need to set it by hand.
# CCMANAGERUI_RELAUNCH=
